The field consists of a rectangle and an equilateral triangle sharing a common side of 42 ft. The rectangle has a length of 76 ft and a width of 42 ft, so its perimeter contribution is two lengths and one width (since the other width is replaced by the triangle's side). The triangle contributes two of its three equal sides (42 ft each) because the third side is shared.

Thus, the total perimeter is \(76 + 76 + 42 + 42 + 42 = 278\) ft.

